### ğŸ” **Step-by-Step Flow Explanation**

#### **STEP 1: Exporters Collect Metrics (On Each Server)**

```
Every second, the exporter reads system stats:

ğŸ§ Linux (Node Exporter)                ğŸªŸ Windows (Windows Exporter)
â”œâ”€â”€ Reads /proc/stat (CPU)              â”œâ”€â”€ Reads WMI/Performance Counters
â”œâ”€â”€ Reads /proc/meminfo (RAM)           â”œâ”€â”€ CPU usage per core
â”œâ”€â”€ Reads /proc/diskstats (Disk I/O)    â”œâ”€â”€ Memory usage
â”œâ”€â”€ Reads /sys/class/net (Network)      â”œâ”€â”€ Disk space per drive
â””â”€â”€ Exposes at :9100/metrics            â””â”€â”€ Exposes at :9182/metrics
```

**What the metrics look like (raw):**
```
# Node Exporter output (Linux)
node_cpu_seconds_total{cpu="0",mode="idle"} 123456.78
node_memory_MemTotal_bytes 8589934592
node_filesystem_avail_bytes{mountpoint="/"} 50000000000

# Windows Exporter output
windows_cpu_time_total{core="0",mode="idle"} 98765.43
windows_os_physical_memory_free_bytes 4294967296
windows_logical_disk_free_bytes{volume="C:"} 100000000000
```

